				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="Curse of the Deathwatcher" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>Players start in a cell, deep in the Deathwatchers dungeon. Their objective is to navigate the dungeon and it&amp;rsquo;s traps to escape. To prevent this, the Deathwatcher sends his curse to hunt the players, killing them on contact. If a player should die, he transforms into a minion of the Deathwatcher. This player can still win by scoring points when he kills other players. Players use standees to move on the gameboard and a charactersheet to keep track of their scores and possessions.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The dungeon is represented by a non-modular map which has several routes of varying length with unexplored rooms that are only revealed when a player enters them and are either a dead end or not. This ensures the need for flexible planning by players. It is up to each player to plot a route through the crypt and modify their plan according to revealed rooms and the actions of other players.&amp;#10;In their turn players must first choose how they move. Either slowly and sneaky to attract less attention and find more treasure or fast and reckless to cover more ground. &amp;#10;Then they roll the dungeon die to see what happens to him or her that round. This will be highly influenced by the choice of movement.&amp;#10;Lastly they must deal with obstacles like traps or combat which occurs when a player draws a monster card or when a player that became a servant of the Deathwatcher catches a still living player.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
